history.content:
The waitlist is some crazy stuff as students get shifted around due to what discussion section they're in etc. Sit tight and in the long run your waitlist position should improve. 

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

In response to the initial response from the instructors, should we then expect our waitlist position to move back up when these students are added back into the class? Because it still appears that the class is full to the 70% enrollment cap, but I have shifted back five places on the waitlist at this point.  This makes me believe that it can't really be that explanation.
The waitlist is some crazy stuff as students get shifted around due to what discussion section they're in etc. Sit tight and in the long run your waitlist position should improve.

This is a little hard to explain so bear with me: In the new system, once a waitlist is formed, everyone is waitlisted when they try and change anything, including enrolled students who want to switch secondary sections. What I'm guessing is happening is that enrolled students are switching, then sent to the waitlist at position #1, then if the sections they chose are open, they're enrolled when the waitlist is processed automatically. If they are enrolled, your number should go back to 81. If the sections they chose are full, you would remain at 82.

Does this make sense or does it seem like something else is happening?

Hi, I'm a 3rd year EECS major, and I added myself to the waitlist for CS 189. The discussion time I added myself was "open" (with a waitlist that still was less than the number of open seats).

Yesterday at 1PM I was at position 81; today morning I was at 82; now when I check I'm at position 84. How is it possible for me to shift /down/ the waitlist?
